citation.case_name: MISSOURI, KANSAS & TEXAS RAILWAY CO. v. Kennedy

html:
214 U.S. 502

29 S.Ct. 699

53 L.Ed. 1061

MISSOURI, KANSAS, & TEXAS RAILWAY COMPANY OF TEXAS et al., Plaintiffs in Error,
v.
S. M. KENNEDY.

No. 817.

May 3, 1909.

Messrs. James Hagerman, J. M. Bryson, and A. B. Browne for plaintiffs in error.

1

Mr. Charles A. Culberson for defendant in error.

2

Dismissed for want of jurisdiction.
